com.bluegosling.reflect

Interface AnnotatedTypeVisitor<R,P>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of value returned from visiting a type
    P - an optional context parameter that is supplied to the visitor when visiting a type

    public interface AnnotatedTypeVisitor<R,P>
    A visitor for annotated types. This enables dynamic-dispatch-like algorithms without the if-else boiler-plate with instanceof checks and casts. To visit a type, use the main entry-point method: visit(AnnotatedType, Object).

    • Method Detail

      • visit

        default R visit(AnnotatedType type,
                P param)
        Visits the given type. This is the entry point and generally need not be overridden by implementing classes. This method will re-dispatch to one of the other visit methods based on the kind of given type.

        If the given type is not a known sub-interface of AnnotatedType then the default action is invoked. This is the expected case when the annotated type is a non-generic declared type, a raw type (e.g. an instance of a generic declared type with no type parameters), or a primitive type. It could also happen for unknown kinds of annotated types.

        Parameters:
        type - the type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type

      • defaultAction

        default R defaultAction(AnnotatedType type,
                        P param)
        The default action for visiting a type, called when visiting a type where the corresponding visit* method has not been overridden.

        The default implementation returns null.

        Parameters:
        type - an annotated type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type

      • visitOtherType

        default R visitOtherType(AnnotatedType type,
                         P param)
        Invoked when the visited type is not suitable for one of the more specific visit* methods. This happens when the underlying type is a non-generic declared type, a raw type (a generic type with no type arguments), or a primitive type.

        This could also happen for unknown or unexpected kinds of AnnotatedType.

        Parameters:
        type - an annotated type
        param - the context parameter
        Returns:
        the result of visiting the given type
